===Etymology===
From [[Middle English]] from [[Old French]] {{term|palais|lang=fr}}, which comes from {{etyl|la}} {{term|Palatium|Palātium|lang=la}}, in reference to the [[Palatine]] Hill, one of the seven hills of Rome, where the aristocracy of the Roman [[Republic]] and—later, Roman emperors—built large, splendid residences.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/'pæləs/}}
* {{audio|en-us-palace.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Official residence of a head of state or other dignitary.
# A large and lavishly ornate residence.
# A large, ornate public building used for entertainment or exhibitions.

